message.content: cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a large-scale knowledge base for reasoning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves natural language processing, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
